The paper deals with the construction of pseudorandom generators, which is a central topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The use of the discrete Fourier transform is a key technique in the construction, which suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.IT (information theory). The paper also mentions several classes of tests that the pseudorandom generator can fool, including halfspaces and combinatorial shapes, which are topics in computational geometry and discrete mathematics, respectively (cs.DS, cs.DM). Finally, the paper involves some novel analytic machinery, which could potentially fall under the category of cryptography (cs.CR).
